last_episode_to_air.name: Castleton Tower
last_episode_to_air.overview: Driven by a dream to camp out overnight on the side of a cliff in a portaledge, Juanpa enlists a professional vertical climber to initiate him into the world of climbing culture. After some brief but intense training, Juanpa and his climbing coaches attempt to scale the awe-inspiring 400-foot Castleton Tower in Castle Valley, Utah. With no family or close friends to lean on, Juanpa must marshal all of his fortitude to reach the summit.

name: Carpe DM with Juanpa
overview: Social media star Juanpa Zurita travels to the U.S. for 6 heart-pounding adventures. From riding a bucking bronco to attempting the flying trapeze, Juanpa puts it all on the line.

episodes.name: Ride a Bronco
episodes.overview: Juanpa and fellow social media star and close friend, Mario Ruiz, dive into cowboy culture when they travel to Texas and Oklahoma to work as ranch hands and train with a professional rodeo coach. Ultimately, both Juanpa and Mario attempt to cram a lifetime of arduous training into a 3-day adventure with the goal of accomplishing one of the most difficult and dangerous sports feats in the world: riding a bucking bronco for 8 seconds.

episodes.name: Mt. Rainier
episodes.overview: In a harrowing and dangerous adventure, Juanpa and his girlfriend, Macarena Achaga, head to just outside Seattle, Washington to attempt to climb the tallest mountain in the Cascade Mountain range.

episodes.name: Monster Jam
episodes.overview: Juanpa goes on an adventure to live out a childhood dream in the world of monster trucks. Joining him is his friend Juca Viapri, a car and truck expert. Together, they travel to Cleveland, Ohio where they take giant construction vehicles through an obstacle course, meet a monster truck superfan who builds his own behemoth machines, and ultimately train with Monster Jam champion Tom Meents, who gives Juanpa a chance to prove that he is capable of jumping a 14,000-pound monster truck.

episodes.name: 10Gs
episodes.overview: Juanpa brings his reluctant sister, Pau, along for this gravity-defying adventure. First, they get true F35 simulator training at Lockheed Martin. Then, they experience the sensation of G-forces while drifting in Lamborghinis going over 200 mph. And finally, both Juanpa and Pau find out what "aerobatics" actually feel like, as they attempt to reach a staggering 10Gs of force in sky combat planes.

episodes.name: Flying Trapeze
episodes.overview: Juanpa is joined by his brother Andres in Las Vegas, where they learn to do battle on the Ka stage before trapeze legend Renato Fernandes trains them to fly through the air...with no safety lines!
